				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Howdy all !   casual playing 59th mage on veeshan here.
<br />

<br />
Although players can now breeze thru level 50s via PoP zones, it is still painful to see how our pets have gone from good ADDS off-tank to "the few seconds" buffer to head off to zoneline.  Anyway, now that Rytan is paying us some attention, I'd like to share my thoughts on some possible ideas to improve us mages : 
<br />

<br />
1> resists adjust for our rain spells (IMO clearly our most effective DPS spells in our lv 50s)
<br />

<br />
2> upgraded summoned armour (that actually makes a good impact to pet's AC and mitigation) as well as a less-procing (50 pt DD) wpn for pets
<br />

<br />
3> here's the big one: OK! our GV pets are HARDLY an upgrade to our V pets!!  One possible and REAL upgrade would be for that GV pet spell to actually summon TWO pets that are both equivalent to the V pet.  
<br />
Adv: two pets mean 2x pets DPS, 2x procs (stuns!!), 2x speedbumps (survivability).  To compensate such great power of us MASTER of all summoner,  the spell will require a peridot, consumes 3x the mana as to summon a V pet.   ALtho with 2 pets, they will be commanded via the (existing) one pet window which means the pets will ALWAYS obey the same command and attack the same mob.  The real drawback will be the 30 min recast time, also you cannot cast this spell even if only one of the pets has died (both pets must be dead before a new summon is possible).  Chaining is still possible..... but once every 30 mins , now that wouldn't be overpowered?
<br />
 <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
re:pet heals, maybe each pet will receive half the HPs each?
<br />

<br />
Do you think the suggestions are reasonable at all ? or am i living in day-dream island again?  
<br />

<br />
Aruthar 
<br />
59 th mage on veeshan<br />_________________<br />Aruthar &lt; Fellowship of Vallor&gt;
<br />
58 Mage -- Veeshan</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
