			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">OK I will expand then.
<br />

<br />
The Zomm pet should work exactly like it does, poofing when there is no one left to vent its rage on.  I would have it be a bit more damaging than it currently is, since by all accounts, it attacks less often than its permanent counterparts.  In a perfect situation with a perfect pull and tank switch combination, you can keep the pet up as long as there is something it can aggro on.  One AE mez and the pet is likely to be history though.
<br />

<br />
The Decoy pet doesnt initiate actual attacks, it just (AE?) taunts, and taunts, and taunts.  Pet back off will shut it up unless it reaggros like any normal pet would,  pet hold will shut it up until pet attack starts it up again.  Pet No Taunt would be ignored by the decoy.  Since we know that a DS just doesnt cut it anymore, why not just give the Decoy a very high avoidance and a good riposte chance, and good general defense and HP, about like a well equipped monk?  Will this be a big help mostly?  No, in most situations, the pet will not be getting hit, but it may well make a difference on an add or if the tank goes down.  It might save the day every once in a while, and in a way that is perfectly in tune with the mages idiom.  With the Decoy, you lose the extra damage a Zomm pet/spam pets/flappy would do, but it will give the party a bit of extra security.  If you named the Decoy [Rondo]s Decoy it would also shield us, but at the considerable loss of its ripostes.  That actually might be a weakness to the pet, not really sure though.  I do rather like the thought of that naming schema though.  I would enjoy seeing the message Soandso has been slain by Rondos Rage.  The higher level versions could be tagged [Rondo]s Wrath and [Rondo]s Deception.  The Decoys Achilles Heal will of course be casters.  Its riposte and dodge wont help against spells and AEs, and casters seem to be less affected by taunts than melee mobs.  Now, if your low resist is in the 275 to 300 range, your decoy wont be taking much spell damage, but it also wont be generating aggro through ripostes.
<br />

<br />
Would we be able to solo with a Decoy and a water pet?  If you were careful to use regular back offs so that the water pet didnt grab aggro, and the decoy would reaggro and start to taunt again when it took an attack you could probably do well against a lot of mobs.  POE and probably POF mobs would still eat through the Decoy too fast to be terribly efficient, but maybe.  Now if you had a 100% riposte decoy you would be devastation, /em dreams of glory and mayhem, but that would be just too over the top, and definitely would be used/abused to the detriment of player tanks.<br />_________________<br />Rondo</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
