			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I had actually figured that they would be *stupid* pets like the spam pets or the the Flappy.  They would follow the same instructions as your regular pet, thus hitting /pet back off will kill your Rage pet since its aggro list will be cleared.  My original thought would hav the Decoy be unmoving but hopefully would also be summoned with the summon companion spell.  After a bit I decided that there would be a few ways to exploit this, so just having it autofollow the mage would have to do.
<br />

<br />
I think two separate pet commands would add a whole lot of extra programming, and potential for server crashing new problems.  I don't think it would be worth it.
<br />

<br />
