			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I like this idea alot actually, and it could be a viable answer to post-60 soloing.  If we're allowed to make our own small pet chain we could effectively solo teir 3+ mobs, using an ability that has been unique to the magician class throughout EQ history.  As a downside, make it so that you could only have 1 type of pet up at a time, so you couldn't stun-lock mobs with 2 air pets.  This would also require the mage to keep 2 different pet spells mem'd at all times when soloing.  It would effectively double our pet DPS, which would put us right where we need to be balance wise.  Also, ALL our pet spells would need to have the auto-pet-targeting thing removed, so we could target each pet indivdually, including Suspend Minion.  
<br />

<br />
Make it a class AA ability that costs 9 points and replaces turn summoned, so mages at level 59 could start using it (which is about when I think we start having serious problems).  Keep the current pet summoning spells exactly the way they are, no need for them to cost peridots or have super long recast times.  
<br />

<br />
Damn, the more I think about it the more brilliant this idea seems!  Thanks Aruthar!<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370607" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Tiiden Vandorgriffin</a>
<br />
65 Magician, Rodcet Nife</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
