				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">WOW!! didn't know my idea would echo similar ideas from all ya mages!  keep them coming guys and I hope Rytan and the devs are reading!  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
The reason why I suggested two pets and they are to be commanded under the same pet-window is because this is already in place -- therefore making it simpler for the devs to simply allow for the 2nd pet.  Hell come think of it, perhaps let's NOT look at this as allowing us mages to have multiple pets,  but to allow a mage (by means of a spell or AA) to summon ELEMENTAL TWINS!!  yep! and so they will obey to the same one command from the pet-window.   and again, for balance purpose one cannot recast this spell/AA unless BOTH pets are dead, and the recast time be reasonable to prevent pet chaining. <img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="Cool" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
let's say this is to be a lv 59 spell/AA, each of the TWINS will be a slightly toned down version of the Vocerate pets but retaining their class defining abilities.  IMO this will slightly improve our soloability and greatly improve our desirability in groups.  Solo wise, two toned down G pets should last a few more seconds against a PoI yardtrash if we nuke hard enough, and the recast delay will prevent us from being overpowered.   Grouping wise, in the presence of a player tank, our TWINS will deal almost, 2x DPS and 2x procs/spells.  Heck we may even be able to off-tank adds once again with this TWINS.  
<br />

<br />
pet heals : allowing each pet to receive half the HPs would definitely keep things under balanced as well.  
<br />

<br />
I love the idea about having an elemental pet and a monster/zomm/decoy pet as well but i thought the elemental twins idea would be easier to code, that's all.  
