				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I wasn't really thinking of 2 full pets. (It would be fun however)
<br />

<br />
I really do think that the upgraded Rage and Decoy pets as I described would be enough to put mages back in the game.  Rage would be an on demand burst damage, and Decoy would be a good defense, and on tauntable mobs would help keep the mob on the melee, since the decoys would be high up on the aggro list, and would be able to tank well enough for emergencies.
<br />

<br />
Rage should be a very fast cast pet, since it will be too lightweight versus Melee to be useful chaining so needs no balancing, but Decoy should have a relatively long cast time or, preferably, refresh time to keep from making pet chaining trivial, which I think is the serious problem with two full pets.  With two independantly targettable pets, reclaim chaining against any mob that doesn't kill so fast that enrage fails would be nearly risk and mana free, along with fast kills.  We would become the de facto dragon solo Lords of Norrath, doing it much easier than anyone else.<br />_________________<br />Rondo</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
