			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't think that giving magicians two pets, even toned down, is a good idea. Consider this...
<br />

<br />
So, for the GVoc level, you get a Vocerate type pet, but you get two of them. Well, if you choose two air pets, your pets stuns just got twice as good, and provided they're spaced out, can keep a mob well stunned, just solo. That in itself is kind of powerful.
<br />

<br />
Alternatively, the level difference between Vocerate pets and GVoc pets is noticable. While level may not affect pet resist rates, it affects the pets ability to hit and land spells. Lower level, but x2 pets, means that the pets will suffer in being able to land on mobs and hit them well, you just get two to do a little more damage. Not a good solution for me.
<br />

<br />
Fire and Forget pets might be an acceptable alternative to having two pets up, but then, we get that now with AA's. Servant of Ro is about 1 free nuke's worth over a 2 minute timespan. Host is massive damage in 30 seconds. These are our secondary pets at the higher end. Add on another swarm pet that we can fire (Rage or DDD), and not only are we the spam kings (how many pets can you have at once, 13?) but may lean towards overpowering us over a short haul.
<br />

<br />
Just something to consider.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
